ds, tensorlib.isfinite(summands))\r\n+        # tosum = tensorlib.boolean_mask(summands, tensorlib.isfinite(summands))\r\n+        tosum = summands\r\n         mainpdf = tensorlib.sum(tosum)\r\n         return mainpdf\r\n```\r\n\r\nsince bool-based indexing  seems to not work\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport pyhf\r\nimport numpy as onp\r\n\r\npyhf.set_backend(pyhf.tensor.jax_backend())\r\n\r\nm = pyhf.simplemodels.hepdata_like(signal_data = [5.], bkg_data = [17.], bkg_uncerts = [2.])\r\ntestdata = m.expected_data(m.config.suggested_init())\r\ntestpars = m.config.suggested_init()\r\nvalue = m.logpdf(testpars,testdata)\r\n\r\nprint(type(value))\r\nprint(onp.asarray(value))\r\n```\r\n\r\nlocally this gives\r\n\r\n```\r\n/Users/lukas/Code/pyhfdev/venv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/jax/lib/xla_bridge.py:143: UserWarning: No GPU found, falling back to CPU.\r\n  warnings.warn('No GPU found, falling back to CPU.')\r\n<class 'jax.interpreters.xla.DeviceArray'>\r\n[-5.528393]\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/google/jax/issues/166\r\n\r\n# Checklist Before Requesting Reviewer\r\n\r\n- [x] Tests are passing\r\n- [x] \"WIP\" removed from the title of the pull request\r\n- [x] Selected an Assignee for the PR to be responsible for the log summary\r\n\r\n# Before Merging\r\n\r\nFor the PR Assignees:\r\n\r\n- [x] Summarize commit messages into a comprehensive review of the PR\r\n\r\n```\r\n* add JAX backend\r\n```", "created_at": "2018-12-21T21:23:12Z", "updated_at": "2020-01-13T00:58:43Z", "closed_at": "2020-01-13T00:58:42Z", "merged_at": "2020-01-13T00:58:41Z", "merge_commit_sha": "eb9944c043f7f8a75b9cfe6f8bd781bd1dd7014b", "assignees": [{"login": "lukasheinrich", "id": 2318083, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTgwODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2318083?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich", "html_url": "https://github.com/lukasheinrich", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lukasheinrich/followers", "following_url": "ht